          <td class="mainbody">

<span class="headers">Help Keep the Site Running and Ad-Free!</span>
<p>
            <table width="90%" border="0">
              <tr>
                <td><img src="http://www.eqtraders.com/images/articles/gu_20010211.jpg" border="0" hspace="20" align="left"/>
                <td>
                  <p>There are many expenses that come with running this site, 
                    and as the popularity of EQTC grows, so do the costs. It is 
                    no longer feasible for us to pay for the costs by ourselves, 
                    so we're asking for the help of those in the community who 
                    are able to contribute. <i>(FYI: All of the first two years, 
                    including domain name registrations, EZBoard fees, software 
                    and hardware costs were covered by the DenMother and House 
                    Ogre. Since December 2001, we've accepted donations, but they 
                    do not cover the growing costs of running this site.)</i> 
                    While we're thrilled that the site has become so popular, 
                    the surge in traffic is really starting to cost money, especially 
                    now that it's become so costly to keep the message boards 
                    free of ads. (Not to mention a solid 60-80 hours a week of 
                    combined time from the DenMother and the House Ogre while 
                    the database is being built/developed.)</p>
                  <p>We really <i><b>DO</b></i> want to keep the boards ad-free, 
                    and continue to maintain our new tradeskill database, but we cannot 
                    do it without the support of the community.</p>
                  <p>Currently, we have only the one method for donating to the 
                    site, though we may work out a second alternative for those 
                    of you who have problems with Paypal accounts for any reason:</p>
                  <p><b>Paypal</b> - donations go directly to the DemMother to 
                    help cover the new hosting costs, message board costs, software/hardware 
                    expenses, etc. If there's any left over (there usually isn't), 
                    it will go to cover things for Niami like asprin, chocolate, 
                    massage therapy, ... and hair color to hide the grey hairs 
                    that the site has caused ... consider it her "pay" 
                    for the amount of work put into this site. ;)</p>
            </td>
              </tr>
            </table>
